EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to mental health; establishing provisions related to
the discharge of a child with an emotional disturbance
from certain inpatient psychiatric treatment facilities;
establishing a task force to develop recommendations for
the creation of a program that provides housing and other
services to certain children who are discharged from a
treatment facility or certain other facilities or released on
parole; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law imposes certain requirements concerning the treatment of a child
2 with an emotional disturbance. (NRS 433B.290-433B.339) Section 3 of this bill
3 requires a public or private inpatient psychiatric treatment facility that admits a
4 child with an emotional disturbance to establish discharge procedures which
5 prohibit a child from being discharged to a temporary facility unless the temporary
6 facility is the only facility that is available to receive the child for treatment.
7 Section 2.6 of this bill requires the Division of Child and Family Services of
8 the Department of Health and Human Services to establish a task force to develop
9 recommendations for the creation of a program that provides housing and other
10 services to certain children: (1) who are discharged from a treatment facility or
11 other division facility or who are released on parole or discharged from a state
12 facility for the detention of children; and (2) whose parents or guardians are unable
13 to accept the child back into the home after the discharge or release because of a
14 health or safety risk. Section 2.6 requires the Administrator of the Division to
15 appoint representatives of the child welfare, juvenile justice and mental health
16 systems to the task force. Section 2.8 of this bill establishes certain criteria for the
