17 recommendations and requires the recommendations to be submitted to the Joint
18 Interim Standing Committee on Health and Human Services.
19 Existing law defines certain terms, including, “child with an emotional
20 disturbance” for the purposes of chapter 433B of NRS related to the mental health
21 of children. (NRS 433B.020-433B.100) Section 6 of this bill revises the definition
22 of “child with an emotional disturbance” to provide that the term includes, without
23 limitation, a child with a severe emotional disturbance. (NRS 433B.045)
24 Sections 7 and 9 of this bill remove and repeal certain provisions that contain a
25 definition of “agency which provides child welfare services” for the purpose of
26 consolidating the provisions into a single definition under section 2.4 of this bill.
27 Section 5 of this bill makes a conforming change to indicate that the consolidated
28 definition of “agency which provides child welfare services” applies to the
29 provisions of chapter 433B of NRS. Section 8 of this bill makes a conforming
30 change related to the consolidated definition.
